-- PFM Group Names Robert J. Delany as Finance Chief
-- B y   R o m y   V a r g h e s e
-- 2012-09-12T19:22:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-12/pfm-group-names-robert-j-delany-as-finance-chief.html
Robert J. Delany will become PFM
Group’s chief financial officer and managing director in the
financial adviser’s Philadelphia headquarters, according to a
statement from the company.  Delany was previously the CFO of Sciens Capital Management
LLC in  New York , PFM said today in the  statement . Earlier, he
was chief operating officer for Europe at American Financial
Realty Trust/European Financial Realty.  “Orchestrating and funding PFM’s strategic growth involves
many complex and demanding tasks, and we sought an executive
with broad experience in many areas of finance,” John H. Bonow,
PFM’s chief executive officer, said in the statement. “Rob is
such a professional and we are eager to work with him.”  PFM Group is the parent of Public Financial Management, the
largest  investment adviser  in the U.S. municipal bond market.
The unit was ranked first in proceeds and number of deals among
advisers in 2011 by Thomson Reuters. The unit worked on 757
transactions involving $39.6 billion last year, according to
 Thomson Reuters .  Delany lives in Maple Glen, Pennsylvania.  To contact the reporter on this story:
